Pregnant Kim Kardashian craves for giant cookies
Socialite Kim Kardashian, who is expecting her first child with her boyfriend Kanye West in early June, is battling serious cravings for junk food, says her mother Kris Jenner.
"Kim is doing great. She is having craving for giant cookies from BJs. Last night she craved French fries, Chinese chicken salad and artichokes," Kris, 57, told eonline.com.
Kim Kardashian's older sister Kourtney Kardashian, who has two children, Mason, 7, and seven-month-old Penelope, previously revealed that she also craved junk food during her second pregnancy last year.
"I remember when I first got pregnant with Mason. I wanted fruit and frozen yogurt and all this healthy stuff. This time it's like cheeseburgers, sour cream and onion chips and double-stuffed Oreos," she said.﻿
